HEADWORD: Shorthand
<hw>Short"hand`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A compendious and
rapid method or writing by substituting characters, abbreviations, or
symbols, for letters, words, etc.; short writing; stenography.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Short-handed</ent>⟦br⟧
